## Design Direction for New Build\
\
### Keep From Current Site\
- The dark navy/teal blue color (`#004D78` or similar) \'97 it's medical and trustworthy\
- Lato font or similar clean sans-serif\
- White text on dark backgrounds\
- Rounded corners (but more subtle \'97 12-16px, not 37px)\
- Clean, minimal aesthetic\
\
### Change / Improve\
- Add a secondary accent color for CTAs (e.g., a warm orange `#F59E0B` or green `#10B981` for "Book Now" buttons to create contrast)\
- Use a proper grid system that works on all screen sizes\
- Replace the massive circle-cropped hero image with a professional full-width hero banner or a more contained image\
- Use proper iconography (medical icons from Lucide, Heroicons, or custom SVGs) instead of tiny photo thumbnails for screening types\
- Add gradient overlays on hero sections for text readability\
- Ensure contrast ratios meet WCAG AA standards\
- Use proper spacing scale (no more 800px white gaps)\
- Add subtle animations (fade-in on scroll) but make sure they work \'97 the current Carrd site appears to have broken scroll-triggered animations\
\
### Brand Assets Needed\
- Logo: The circular "Signal View Ultrasound" logo (currently image07.jpg) \'97 request an SVG version\
- Hero imagery: Professional photos of the screening process, equipment, clinic\
- Social proof: Patient testimonials, Google review screenshots, star ratings\
- Team photos: The sonographer(s) / medical staff\
